A pop-up with single or multiple selection is used as a form control. 
      oxy_popup. This type of form control supports the following properties:

.
          For the Pop-up form control, its value has to be popupSelection;






;In case the value of the rows property is not specifies,
            the default value of 12 is used.

;This property is used for rendering in the Author
            mode.

;

;

;

;The value of the resultSeparator property cannot exceed one
            character.

;

labels - specifies the label associated with each entry used for
          presentation. In case this property is not specified, the values
          property is used as label;

. This property is used for the visual representation of the form control;

;

;

;

. To make the Pop-up form control inherit its font from its parent element, set the
            fontInherit property to true;In the
            below example, the value of the fontInherit property is
              true, meaning that the pop-up form control inherits the font
            size of 30px from the font-size
          property.
